  "root_text": {
    "iti40:0.1": "Itivuttaka 40 ",
    "iti40:0.2": "Dukanipāta ",
    "iti40:0.3": "Dutiyavagga ",
    "iti40:0.4": "Vijjāsutta ",
    "iti40:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti40:2.1": "“Avijjā, bhikkhave, pubbaṅgamā akusalānaṁ dhammānaṁ samāpattiyā anvadeva ahirikaṁ anottappaṁ; ",
    "iti40:2.2": "vijjā ca kho, bhikkhave, pubbaṅgamā kusalānaṁ dhammānaṁ samāpattiyā anvadeva hirottappan”ti. ",
    "iti40:2.3": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti40:2.4": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti40:3.1": "“Yā kācimā duggatiyo, ",
    "iti40:3.2": "asmiṁ loke paramhi ca; ",
    "iti40:3.3": "Avijjāmūlikā sabbā, ",
    "iti40:3.4": "icchālobhasamussayā. ",
    "iti40:4.1": "Yato ca hoti pāpiccho, ",
    "iti40:4.2": "ahirīko anādaro; ",
    "iti40:4.3": "Tato pāpaṁ pasavati, ",
    "iti40:4.4": "apāyaṁ tena gacchati. ",
    "iti40:5.1": "Tasmā chandañca lobhañca, ",
    "iti40:5.2": "avijjañca virājayaṁ; ",
    "iti40:5.3": "Vijjaṁ uppādayaṁ bhikkhu, ",
    "iti40:5.4": "sabbā duggatiyo jahe”ti. ",
    "iti40:6.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti40:6.2": "Tatiyaṁ. ",
    "iti40:6.3": "Paṭhamabhāṇavāro. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti40:0.1": "So It Was Said 40 ",
    "iti40:0.2": "The Book of the Twos ",
    "iti40:0.3": "Chapter Two ",
    "iti40:0.4": "Knowledge ",
    "iti40:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti40:2.1": "“Mendicants, ignorance precedes the attainment of unskillful qualities, with lack of conscience and prudence following along. ",
    "iti40:2.2": "Knowledge precedes the attainment of skillful qualities, with conscience and prudence following along.” ",
    "iti40:2.3": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti40:2.4": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti40:3.1": "“Bad destinies of whatever kind, ",
    "iti40:3.2": "in this world or the next, ",
    "iti40:3.3": "are all rooted in ignorance, ",
    "iti40:3.4": "compounded of greed and desire. ",
    "iti40:4.1": "Since one of corrupt wishes is ",
    "iti40:4.2": "unconscientious, lacking regard for others, ",
    "iti40:4.3": "they brim with much wickedness, ",
    "iti40:4.4": "which sends them to a place of loss. ",
    "iti40:5.1": "Therefore, dispelling desire ",
    "iti40:5.2": "and greed and ignorance, ",
    "iti40:5.3": "a mendicant arousing knowledge ",
    "iti40:5.4": "would abandon all bad destinies.” ",
    "iti40:6.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti40:4.2": "ahirīko → ahiriko (sya-all) "
  },
